2.0    (15.02.95)   Complete rewrite. Not a single line of code was
                    kept from the 1.5 release. Some of new new features:
                      - make guides from the include files
                      - new format for table of contents (the "MAIN" node)
                      - some minor optical improvements (some keywords
                        are now displayed bold)
                      - should be able to correctly distinguish between
                        "functions" and "defined constants" (important for
                        converting the MUI autodocs)
                      - knows about varargs
                      - I tried to think about the problem *before* starting
                        to write code, most of the time.
                      - much much more

2.1    (22.04.95)   - Fixed a stupid bug that would cause ADtoHT to get into
                      an endless loop... until it runs out of memory.
                    - ADtoHT will now ignore any text found before the
                      "TABLE OF CONTENTS" in an autodoc file.
                    - Some minor changes to the source that are not really
                      worth mentioning. However, one of those changes boosts
                      performance by at least 0.000000000000000001%, and the
                      best thing is: ADtoHT is still *free*, despite this
                      incredible speed increase...

